{"type":"message","id":"2d65aef3","parentId":"497be1aa","timestamp":"2026-03-12T13:26:49.262Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_0ee47ed8ec9ffec10169b2bf1195e88191b55394b8df64a01a\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABpsr8SNLIhrJ1gA7dM8LWCKajZQk6jGg_Sx6X0RPIz41UAjXmZQm56fuxw_oicIZbFdehFz2gps9Oh-mB-EvwRDXl-AxPKubpEK360zAPE16NdluE3KRuq2CZMV5sSod_BD94UnwovKuNetjOpntDCos3Po1ZaRXVkIZBGIRm3KwTSr9eWVlB0YAjobHLl78Qukxk3rjM9KWP3kjSaqaTh1y5ueMR4kthAoVREki3kU_MQWjS7AU9yj74LsQh--Q_e-9iGh00NqBBawZAtmNvQ9X3YkaOvgOIyCFAqziceM5LF-auqLJROaiZi_mVeq0kXD18jyPvuFXFS69uM3gsdL6KAOIOCiFuAoCMJGSwhV02C-Oc0PPwBNLPzsUGDhVWDfhblfxPpDb2ixyJupPzJmsgMmilhIZFWPWQ3zaYv7GXYREKIFlTpMR2qS-vMAZ0Q4i94H4h_Pu81tGZ33rjQgiJp3f452lHN2sLkx2nyHsV7pg7yvoww2r2w_EeiZnO7BiJnpY2gPChQYUjsfUCwo9TD9rRu3mWpiXMZGxD3so0pZifobJWjutJbyAlTJN4x2ii1LWszXt4dS4P2dCq8sa-MNjX-q1-knF4bp90eAwlFLGbwFIAO78fUDxwNuLNSuouKS_gCTW5_tcCbmSQNcRTSvzjIt8DZePxd3lX5HLlG5k8qttE1guuEn0Yof2_gZGtv-5SG8Id6yWYmOmU81eu5sBfBEq7-alpv8YCe3ymiG7MBGEyqbphh8Ppa9EebJoMaUvqClwPHuT2nfD_EKtn4yHhP8whI8WCUhcJG8g3Zot_7JPMfCZ4s8pJcVFwpbdkUZxtfBHnAIfQtroyI_XbdjA==\",\"summary\":[]}"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Yes â that `dist` folder is most likely a **build/package output** for a skill.\n\nIn your install, I found:\n\n- `/home/node/.openclaw/skills/dist`\n- `/home/node/.openclaw/skills/dist/user-medical-data-update.skill`\n\nAnd that `.skill` file is essentially a **packaged archive** of the skill contents. I checked inside it, and it contains:\n\n- `user-medical-data-update/SKILL.md`\n- `user-medical-data-update/references/schema.md`\n- `user-medical-data-update/scripts/summarize_user_medical_data.py`\n- `user-medical-data-update/scripts/update_user_medical_data.py`\n\n## What it is\nThink of it as the skillâs **distributable bundle**:\n- the source skill folder is the editable working version\n- the `dist/` folder holds the packaged artifact\n- the `.skill` file is like a zip-style package for moving, importing, sharing, or installing that skill elsewhere\n\n## What it is not\nIt is **not** usually the live source you would edit by hand.  \nIf you want to change the skill, you normally edit the original skill directory, not the packaged `.skill` file.\n\n## Why it appeared\nMost likely, during skill creation or packaging, the skill was **exported/built** into a distributable file, and `dist/` was created to hold that output.\n\n## Practical takeaway\n- **Edit:** source skill folder\n- **Distribute/import/share:** `.skill` file in `dist/`\n\nIf you want, I can also:\n1. identify the exact source folder that produced `user-medical-data-update.skill`, or  \n2. remove the `dist/` artifact if you donât want packaged outputs sitting there.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0ee47ed8ec9ffec10169b2bf122774819188ee5ebce0e97e7e\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":209,"output":387,"cacheRead":22912,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":23508,"cost":{"input":0.0005225000000000001,"output":0.005805,"cacheRead":0.005728,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0120555}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773322000551}}
