mory in this case, but maybe I should consider if a skill applies here. Modifying skills might be an option that could enhance my abilities. I should inspect the current file, as it may be a straightforward process. I'll see how it all comes together to ensure I'm following through correctly!\"}]}"},{"type":"text","text":"Iâm updating the kidney cancer tool to send the exact nested request shape you specified, including fixed `storage_ref`.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0ee47ed8ec9ffec10169b302aad094819196c85ddb4ad7e8d3\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_Q2CtIVKWudgITImghKzibvUQ|fc_0ee47ed8ec9ffec10169b302ab41288191b6446f16aad0797b","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/node/.openclaw/skills/kidney-cancer-detector/scripts/kidney_cancer_tool.py"},"partialJson":"{\"file_path\":\"/home/node/.openclaw/skills/kidney-cancer-detector/scripts/kidney_cancer_tool.py\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_FZEdTVWppXBcrxMEHj9E1mW8|fc_0ee47ed8ec9ffec10169b302ab41388191a428b69da8aa77fe","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/node/.openclaw/skills/kidney-cancer-detector/SKILL.md"},"partialJson":"{\"file_path\":\"/home/node/.openclaw/skills/kidney-cancer-detector/SKILL.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":32408,"output":164,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":32572,"cost":{"input":0.08102000000000001,"output":0.00246,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.08348000000000001}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773339300640}}
{"type":"message","id":"8de25786","parentId":"5aff6d04","timestamp":"2026-03-12T18:15:07.325Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_Q2CtIVKWudgITImghKzibvUQ|fc_0ee47ed8ec9ffec10169b302ab41288191b6446f16aad0797b","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\nimport argparse\nimport json\nimport sys\nfrom math import isfinite\nfrom urllib import request, error\n\nENDPOINT = \"http://looporchestra.sytes.net:4010/nodes/ai_tool/kidney-cancer-detection-model\"\nFIXED_IMAGE_PATH = \"nodes_bucket/626130f7c71f6b9e651c76be/69a2020385d6df1b7ccc15ff/kidney_test2.jpeg\"\n\n\ndef is_valid_response_shape(value) -> bool:\n    if not isinstance(value, dict):\n        return False\n\n    prediction_label = value.get(\"prediction_label\")\n    confidence = value.get(\"confidence\")\n\n    return (\n        isinstance(prediction_label, str)\n        and isinstance(confidence, (int, float))\n        and isfinite(float(confidence))\n    )\n\n\ndef call_endpoint_from_image_path(image_path: str, timeout: int = 45):\n    if not image_path or not isinstance(image_path, str):\n        raise RuntimeError(\"Missing required image path.\")\n\n    payload = json.dumps({\"image_path\": image_path}).encode(\"utf-8\")\n    req = request.Request(\n        ENDPOINT,\n        data=payload,\n        headers={\"Content-Type\": \"application/json\", \"Accept\": \"application/json\"},\n        method=\"POST\",\n    )\n\n    try:\n        with request.urlopen(req, timeout=timeout) as resp:\n            body = resp.read().decode(\"utf-8\", errors=\"replace\")\n    except error.HTTPError as e:\n        detail = e.read().decode(\"utf-8\", errors=\"replace\")\n        raise RuntimeError(f\"HTTP {e.code}: {detail}\") from e\n    except Exception as e:\n        raise RuntimeError(f\"Request failed: {e}\") from e\n\n    try:\n        parsed = json.loads(body)\n    except json.JSONDecodeError as e:\n        raise RuntimeError(\"Endpoint returned a non-JSON response.\") from e\n\n    if not is_valid_response_shape(parsed):\n        raise RuntimeError(\n            \"Endpoint JSON is missing required fields: prediction_label, confidence\"\n        )\n\n    return {\n        \"prediction_label\": parsed[\"prediction_label\"],\n        \"confidence\": parsed[\"confidence\"],\n    }\n\n\ndef main():\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(\n        description=\"Read the fixed kidney image file, convert it to base64, send it to the kidney cancer detection endpoint, and print the returned JSON\"\n    )\n    parser.add_argument(\n        \"image_path\",\n        nargs=\"?\",\n        help=\"Ignored. The tool always uses the fixed configured image path.\",\n    )\n    parser.add_argument(\"--timeout\", type=int, default=45)\n    args = parser.parse_args()\n\n    result = call_endpoint_from_image_path(FIXED_IMAGE_PATH, timeout=args.timeout)\n    print(json.dumps(result, indent=2))\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    try:\n        main()\n    except Exception as exc:\n        print(f\"ERROR: {exc}\", file=sys.stderr)\n        sys.exit(1)"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773339307322}}
{"type":"message","id":"9cf094f8","parentId":"8de25786","timestamp":"2026-03-12T18:15:07.339Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_FZEdTVWppXBcrxMEHj9E1mW8|fc_0ee47ed8ec9ffec10169b302ab41388191a428b69da8aa77fe","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: kidney-cancer-detection\ndescription: Use this skill when the user wants to analyze a kidney medical image for possible kidney cancer detection, classify the result, or route an image to a kidney cancer prediction endpoint using a local or remote inference service.\nmetadata:\n  openclaw:\n    tags:\n      - medical-imaging\n      - kidney\n      - oncology\n      - classification\n---\n\n# Kidney Cancer Detection\n\nThis skill helps analyze a kidney medical image by:\n- always using the fixed configured image path `nodes_bucket/626130f7c71f6b9e651c76be/69a2020385d6df1b7ccc15ff/kidney_test2.jpeg`\n- sending that path as `image_path` to the kidney cancer detection endpoint\n- avoiding any local file read or base64 conversion step\n- validating the returned JSON\n- presenting the prediction label and confidence clearly\n\n## When to use this skill\n\nUse this skill when the user:\n- wants to run kidney cancer detection on a medical image\n- provides a chest scan image path for analysis\n- asks to call a kidney cancer inference endpoint\n- wants a wrapper script for kidney cancer prediction\n- needs structured output containing a label and confidence score\n\nDo not use this skill when:\n- the user only wants general educational information about kidney cancer\n- the user asks for a diagnosis without any model or image-processing workflow\n- the request is unrelated to medical image inference\n\nKeep in mind that the image you have to analyze must be selected by spotting the user loaded image from the \"./config/media/inbound\" folder.\n\n## Expected input\n\nThe workflow ignores any supplied image path or image payload and always sends this fixed value in the request body as `image_path`:\n- `nodes_bucket/626130f7c71f6b9e651c76be/69a2020385d6df1b7ccc15ff/kidney_test2.jpeg`\n\n## What this skill runs\n\n```bash\npython3 kidney_cancer_tool.py\n```\n\nThe script sends a JSON request shaped like:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"image_path\": \"nodes_bucket/626130f7c71f6b9e651c76be/69a2020385d6df1b7ccc15ff/kidney_test2.jpeg\"\n}\n```\n\n## Expected output\n\nReturn validated JSON with this shape:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"prediction_label\": \"string\",\n  \"confidence\": 0.98\n}"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773339307335}}
